# =============================================================================
# Resume Assistant — Environment Variables Template
# =============================================================================
# This file defines ALL environment variables consumed by the Docker Compose
# stack. Copy it to `.env` and fill in the secret values before running
# `docker-compose up`.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#   nano .env
#
# IMPORTANT SECURITY REMINDERS
#   - `.env` is gitignored. Never commit it to version control.
#   - You MUST provide real values for the following variables before
#     starting the stack in production:
#       * VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID   (Google OAuth 2.0 Client ID)
#       * JWT_SECRET              (min 32 chars, generate with openssl)
#       * INTERNAL_API_KEY        (shared secret for backend-ai-service)
#   - All placeholder passwords below (resume_pass, guest) are safe for
#     local development only. Change them before any non-local deployment.
#
# THREE-TIER VARIABLE ORGANIZATION
#   Tier 0 — Docker Compose & Host    : project name, host port mappings
#   Tier 1 — Public-Facing Layer      : frontend build-time variables
#   Tier 2 — Internal Application     : auth, MQ, AI provider keys, models
#   Tier 3 — Data Layer               : PostgreSQL credentials and connection
#
# For a detailed explanation of each variable, see:
#   docs/deployment/environment-variables.md
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# TIER 0: DOCKER COMPOSE & HOST CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# These variables control Docker Compose project naming and host-level port
# bindings. They affect how containers are labeled on the host but do NOT
# change inter-container communication (that is handled by Docker networks).
# =============================================================================

# Docker Compose project name. Used as a prefix for container names, volume
# names, and network names. Keeping it consistent makes cleanup easier:
#   docker-compose -p resume-assistant down
COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME=resume-assistant

# Host port mapped to the frontend Nginx container (container port 80).
# Default is 80. If port 80 is already in use (e.g. by a system web server),
# change this to an alternate port such as 8081.
#   curl -f http://localhost:${FRONTEND_HOST_PORT}/health
FRONTEND_HOST_PORT=80

# =============================================================================
# TIER 1: PUBLIC-FACING LAYER (Frontend Nginx)
# =============================================================================
# Variables in this section are consumed by the frontend build process (Vite)
# and the Nginx runtime. The frontend is the ONLY service exposed to the
# internet; all HTTP/HTTPS traffic enters through this tier.
#
# Security boundary:
#   - The browser loads the React SPA from Nginx.
#   - API calls from the browser use relative paths (e.g. /api/login).
#   - Nginx intercepts /api/* and reverse-proxies to the backend over the
#     public-network. The backend itself is NOT exposed to the host.
# =============================================================================

# Google OAuth 2.0 Client ID. Required for Google Sign-In on the login page.
# Obtain from the Google Cloud Console:
#   https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# Create an "OAuth 2.0 Client ID" of type "Web application" and add
# http://localhost (or your domain) to the Authorized JavaScript origins.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-oauth-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Base URL for frontend API calls. This value is baked into the JavaScript
# bundle at BUILD time.
#
# CRITICAL SECURITY WARNING:
#   This MUST be left EMPTY or set to a RELATIVE path (e.g. `/api`) so that
#   the browser sends requests back to the SAME origin (Nginx). Nginx then
#   reverse-proxies them to the backend over the isolated Docker network.
#
#   If you set an ABSOLUTE URL here (e.g. `http://backend:8080` or
#   `http://localhost:8080`), the browser will attempt to connect DIRECTLY
#   to the backend, bypassing Nginx. This breaks the single-entry-point
#   security model and may expose the backend port to the internet.
#
#   Correct:  VITE_API_BASE_URL=        (empty — browser uses relative URLs)
#   Correct:  VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api    (relative path)
#   Wrong:    VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/api
VITE_API_BASE_URL=

# =============================================================================
# TIER 2: INTERNAL APPLICATION LAYER
# =============================================================================
# This tier contains the backend (Spring Boot), the AI service (FastAPI),
# and the message queue (RabbitMQ). None of these services are exposed to
# the host or the internet. They communicate exclusively through Docker's
# internal DNS resolution on the isolated internal-network and db-network.
#
# The backend spans all three tiers (public + internal + db) and acts as
# the security gateway. The AI service and RabbitMQ live strictly in the
# internal tier. PostgreSQL lives strictly in the database tier.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.1 Authentication & Security
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These secrets protect user sessions (JWT) and inter-service REST calls
# (Internal API Key). They are the two primary defense-in-depth layers.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Symmetric signing key for HS256 JWT tokens. All user-facing API endpoints
# (login, registration, resume upload, job matching) require a valid JWT
# signed with this key.
#
# Requirements:
#   - Minimum 32 characters (256 bits).
#   - Use a cryptographically secure random string.
#
# Generate a strong secret:
#   openssl rand -base64 48
#
# Security impact:
#   - If this key is leaked, an attacker can forge valid JWTs for any user.
#   - Rotating this key forces ALL active users to re-authenticate.
JWT_SECRET=change-this-to-a-long-random-secret-at-least-32-characters

# Shared secret between the backend (Spring Boot) and the AI service
# (FastAPI) REST endpoints. The backend sends this value in the
# X-Internal-API-Key header on every outbound HTTP request to ai-service.
# The ai-service middleware rejects requests with a missing or mismatched
# key (HTTP 401 Unauthorized).
#
# Generate a strong secret:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
#
# If left empty, both services skip the check. This is convenient for local
# development but MUST be set in production.
INTERNAL_API_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.2 Message Queue (RabbitMQ)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RabbitMQ decouples the backend from the AI service via asynchronous
# messaging. The backend publishes commands to ai.queue.*; the AI service
# consumes them and publishes results to backend.queue.*.
#
# Docker network behavior:
#   - RABBITMQ_HOST must be the Docker service name `rabbitmq` (resolved
#     on the internal-network).
#   - Port 5672 is NOT exposed to the host; AMQP traffic stays inside Docker.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Docker DNS hostname of the RabbitMQ container. Do NOT use localhost or
# a host IP here — the backend and ai-service reach RabbitMQ through the
# isolated internal-network.
RABBITMQ_HOST=rabbitmq

# AMQP port. This is the container port, not a host port. RabbitMQ listens
# on 5672 inside the internal-network.
RABBITMQ_PORT=5672

# RabbitMQ management credentials. Override the default guest/guest before
# any non-local deployment.
RABBITMQ_USERNAME=guest
RABBITMQ_PASSWORD=guest

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.3 AI Provider API Keys (LiteLLM-compatible)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The AI service uses LiteLLM as a unified routing layer for multiple LLM
# providers. You configure ONE provider by setting the matching API key and
# using the matching model prefix in LLM_TEXT_MODEL / LLM_VISION_MODEL /
# LLM_EMBEDDING_MODEL.
#
# Examples of provider selection:
#
# Provider 1 — Google AI Studio (Gemini)  [DEFAULT & RECOMMENDED]
#   - Set: GEMINI_API_KEY
#   - Use model prefix: gemini/
#   - Example: gemini/gemini-2.5-flash
#   - No credit card or GCP billing required. Get a free key at:
#     https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
#
# Provider 2 — OpenAI
#   - Set: OPENAI_API_KEY
#   - Use model prefix: openai/
#   - Example: openai/gpt-4o-mini
#
# Provider 3 — Anthropic (Claude)
#   - Set: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#   - Use model prefix: anthropic/
#   - Example: anthropic/claude-3-haiku-20240307
#
# Provider 4 — Local / Self-hosted (Ollama)
#   - Set: OLLAMA_API_BASE to your Ollama endpoint
#   - Use model prefix: ollama/
#   - Example: ollama/llama3
#
# For more details on LiteLLM and provider configuration, see:
# https://docs.litellm.ai/docs/providers
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Google AI Studio API key. Free tier available. This is the default
# provider because it requires no cloud billing account.
GEMINI_API_KEY=replace-with-your-gemini-api-key

# OpenAI API key. Required only if you use an openai/ model prefix.
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Anthropic API key. Required only if you use an anthropic/ model prefix.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Base URL for a local Ollama instance. Used only with ollama/ model prefixes.
# If Ollama runs on the Docker host, use the host-gateway address:
#   OLLAMA_API_BASE=http://host.docker.internal:11434
OLLAMA_API_BASE=http://localhost:11434

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.4 Model Parameters
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These variables select the LLM models and control their behavior. The
# model strings follow the LiteLLM format: <provider>/<model-name>.
#
# Embedding dimension CRITICAL NOTE:
#   LLM_EMBEDDING_MODEL_DIMENSION MUST match the output dimension of the
#   selected embedding model. Mismatched dimensions will cause vector
#   insertion failures in PostgreSQL pgvector.
#
# Common dimension values:
#   - gemini-embedding-001        → 1536
#   - text-embedding-3-small      → 1536
#   - text-embedding-3-large      → 3072
#   - text-embedding-ada-002      → 1536
#   - bge-large-en-v1.5 (Ollama)  → 1024
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Text generation model (resume optimization, conversation, job ranking).
LLM_TEXT_MODEL=gemini/gemini-2.5-flash

# Vision model (PDF/image parsing). Can be the same as the text model
# if the provider supports multimodal input.
LLM_VISION_MODEL=gemini/gemini-2.5-flash

# Embedding model (vector generation for semantic search).
LLM_EMBEDDING_MODEL=gemini/gemini-embedding-001

# Output dimension of the embedding model. Must match the model's spec.
# If you change this after data exists, you must re-index all vectors.
LLM_EMBEDDING_MODEL_DIMENSION=1536

# Sampling temperature. Lower values (e.g. 0.1) produce highly deterministic
# output, which is desirable for structured JSON extraction (resume parsing).
# Higher values (e.g. 0.7) produce more creative but less predictable output.
LLM_TEMPERATURE=0.1

# HTTP timeout for each LLM request (text, vision, embedding). Increase this
# if you experience timeout errors with large documents or slow providers.
LLM_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=60

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.5 AI Service Runtime Settings
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These variables configure the FastAPI AI service worker process, logging,
# and Google Cloud Vertex AI integration.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Google Cloud project ID for Vertex AI. Used only when you select a
# vertex_ai/ model prefix. If you use Google AI Studio (gemini/ prefix),
# this value is ignored.
VERTEX_PROJECT_ID=ser594-ai-service

# Google Cloud region for Vertex AI. Common values: us-central1, us-east1,
# europe-west1, asia-northeast1, and global. Used only with vertex_ai/ model prefix.
VERTEX_LOCATION=us-central1

# Absolute host path to your Google Cloud Service Account JSON key file.
# This file is mounted into the ai-service container as a read-only volume
# at /app/credentials/gcp-service-account.json.
#
# CRITICAL: This MUST be an absolute path on the Docker host.
#   Correct: /home/username/credentials/gcp-key.json
#   Wrong:   ./gcp-key.json        (treated as named volume)
#   Wrong:   gcp-key.json          (treated as named volume)
#
# If you use Google AI Studio (gemini/ prefix) instead of Vertex AI,
# you can leave this empty.
VERTEX_CREDENTIALS=

# Log level for the AI service. Valid values: DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR.
# DEBUG prints full LLM prompts and responses (useful for troubleshooting
# but noisy). INFO is recommended for normal operation.
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.6 Backend REST Callbacks (AI Service → Backend)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The AI service calls backend REST endpoints to upsert batch vectors
# (job vectors, resume vectors) and to perform vector search during job
# matching. These endpoints are protected by the same INTERNAL_API_KEY
# middleware used for backend → ai-service calls.
#
# Docker network behavior:
#   - BACKEND_SERVICE_URL uses the Docker service name `backend` which
#     resolves on the internal-network. Do NOT use localhost or host IP.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Base URL of the backend REST API as seen from the ai-service container.
BACKEND_SERVICE_URL=http://backend:8080

# HTTP timeout (seconds) for single-query backend calls (e.g. vector search).
BACKEND_QUERY_TIMEOUT=5

# HTTP timeout (seconds) for batch upsert operations (e.g. uploading
# hundreds of job vectors after parsing).
BACKEND_BATCH_UPSERT_TIMEOUT=30

# Number of vectors per batch upsert request. Larger batches reduce HTTP
# round-trips but increase memory usage on both sides.
BACKEND_BATCH_SIZE=100

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.7 Spring Boot Backend Profile
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Active Spring Boot profile. Controls Flyway, JWT lifetime, and DDL behavior.
#   dev  — Flyway disabled, 24h JWT, create/update DDL. For local development.
#   prod — Flyway enabled, 1h JWT, validate DDL. For production.
SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=dev

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.8 Spring Boot Application Base
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These variables control the basic identity and behavior of the backend
# Spring Boot application.
# 这些变量控制后端 Spring Boot 应用的基本标识和行为。

# Application name displayed in Spring Boot Actuator and logs.
# Spring Boot 应用名称，显示在 Actuator 和日志中。
SPRING_APPLICATION_NAME=resume-assistant-backend

# Whether to enable Flyway database migrations. Overrides the profile default.
#   true  — Run migration scripts on startup (recommended for production).
#   false — Skip migrations (dev default; use init.sql instead).
# 是否启用 Flyway 数据库迁移。覆盖配置文件默认值。
#   true  — 启动时执行迁移脚本（生产环境推荐）。
#   false — 跳过迁移（开发环境默认值；使用 init.sql 代替）。
SPRING_FLYWAY_ENABLED=false

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.9 JWT Token Lifetime
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Token expiration times in milliseconds. Only effective when the backend
# reads them from environment variables (dev profile does; prod profile
# defaults to 1h / 7 days unless overridden).
# 令牌过期时间（毫秒）。仅在后端从环境变量读取时生效
#（dev 配置文件会读取；prod 配置文件默认为 1小时 / 7天，除非被覆盖）。

# Access token expiration (milliseconds).
#   dev default: 86400000 (24 hours)
#   prod default: 3600000 (1 hour)
# Access Token 过期时间（毫秒）。
JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRATION=86400000

# Refresh token expiration (milliseconds). Same for dev and prod.
#   default: 604800000 (7 days)
# Refresh Token 过期时间（毫秒）。开发/生产环境默认值相同。
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRATION=604800000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.10 AI Service Connection
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# URL of the AI service REST API as seen from the backend container.
# 从后端容器视角看到的 AI 服务 REST API 地址。
#
# Docker note: docker-compose.yml hardcodes this to http://ai-service:8000
# for the backend container, so changing this in .env has no effect when
# running inside Docker. Use this only for non-Docker deployments.
# Docker 注意：docker-compose.yml 已为后端容器硬编码此值为
# http://ai-service:8000，因此在 Docker 内运行时修改 .env 无效。
# 仅用于非 Docker 部署。
AI_SERVICE_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.11 File Storage Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The backend supports pluggable storage backends: minio, local, s3, oss.
# Switching storage source only requires changing STORAGE_TYPE and the
# corresponding backend variables below.
# 后端支持可插拔存储后端：minio、local、s3、oss。
# 切换存储源只需修改 STORAGE_TYPE 和下方对应的后端变量。
#
# Docker note: docker-compose.yml hardcodes STORAGE_TYPE=local and
# LOCAL_STORAGE_BASE_PATH=/app/uploads for the backend container.
# Remove those lines in docker-compose.yml if you want .env values to take effect.
# Docker 注意：docker-compose.yml 已为后端容器硬编码 STORAGE_TYPE=local
# 和 LOCAL_STORAGE_BASE_PATH=/app/uploads。若希望 .env 值生效，请在
# docker-compose.yml 中删除对应行。

# Storage backend type. / 存储后端类型。
#   minio — Self-hosted S3-compatible object storage.
#   local — Filesystem storage inside the container (Docker volume).
#   s3    — Amazon AWS S3 or any S3-compatible service.
#   oss   — Aliyun Object Storage Service.
STORAGE_TYPE=minio

# ----------------------------------------
# MinIO Settings (effective when STORAGE_TYPE=minio)
# MinIO 配置（当 STORAGE_TYPE=minio 时生效）
# ----------------------------------------
MINIO_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:9000
MINIO_ACCESS_KEY=minioadmin
MINIO_SECRET_KEY=minioadmin
MINIO_BUCKET_NAME=resumes
MINIO_CONNECT_TIMEOUT=5000
MINIO_WRITE_TIMEOUT=60000
MINIO_READ_TIMEOUT=30000

# ----------------------------------------
# Local Storage Settings (effective when STORAGE_TYPE=local)
# 本地存储配置（当 STORAGE_TYPE=local 时生效）
# ----------------------------------------
LOCAL_STORAGE_BASE_PATH=./uploads
LOCAL_STORAGE_RESUME_PATH=resumes
LOCAL_STORAGE_DATE_SUBDIR=true
LOCAL_STORAGE_URL_PREFIX=

# ----------------------------------------
# AWS S3 Settings (effective when STORAGE_TYPE=s3)
# AWS S3 配置（当 STORAGE_TYPE=s3 时生效）
# ----------------------------------------
# AWS region, e.g. us-east-1, ap-northeast-1, cn-north-1
# AWS 区域，如 us-east-1, ap-northeast-1, cn-north-1
AWS_S3_REGION=us-east-1
# Custom endpoint for S3-compatible third-party storage (MinIO, Ceph).
# Leave empty to use the official AWS endpoint.
# 兼容 S3 的第三方存储自定义端点（MinIO、Ceph）。留空则使用 AWS 官方端点。
AWS_S3_ENDPOINT=
AWS_S3_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_S3_SECRET_KEY=
AWS_S3_BUCKET_NAME=
# true=PathStyle, false=VirtualHostedStyle
AWS_S3_PATH_STYLE=false
AWS_S3_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT=5000
AWS_S3_SOCKET_TIMEOUT=50000
AWS_S3_MAX_CONNECTIONS=50
AWS_S3_ENCRYPTION_ENABLED=false
AWS_S3_KMS_KEY_ID=

# ----------------------------------------
# Aliyun OSS Settings (effective when STORAGE_TYPE=oss)
# 阿里云 OSS 配置（当 STORAGE_TYPE=oss 时生效）
# ----------------------------------------
# Access endpoint. Public: https://oss-{region}.aliyuncs.com
# 访问域名/端点。外网：https://oss-{region}.aliyuncs.com
ALIYUN_OSS_ENDPOINT=
ALIYUN_OSS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
ALIYUN_OSS_ACCESS_KEY_SECRET=
ALIYUN_OSS_BUCKET_NAME=
# CDN domain for generating access URLs. / 用于生成访问 URL 的 CDN 域名。
ALIYUN_OSS_CDN_DOMAIN=
ALIYUN_OSS_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT=5000
ALIYUN_OSS_SOCKET_TIMEOUT=50000
ALIYUN_OSS_MAX_CONNECTIONS=50
# Download buffer size in KB. / 下载缓冲区大小（KB）。
ALIYUN_OSS_DOWNLOAD_BUFFER=64
# Upload part size in MB (for multipart upload). / 上传分片大小（MB，用于大文件分片上传）。
ALIYUN_OSS_UPLOAD_PART_SIZE=5
# Server-side encryption: AES256, KMS, SM4. Leave empty for no encryption.
# 服务器端加密方式：AES256、KMS、SM4。留空表示不加密。
ALIYUN_OSS_SSE=
ALIYUN_OSS_KMS_KEY_ID=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2.12 Backend Logging Levels
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These variables control the verbosity of backend logs. They are injected
# into Spring Boot logging configuration.
# 这些变量控制后端日志的详细程度，注入到 Spring Boot 日志配置中。

# Hibernate SQL log level.
#   DEBUG — Prints every SQL statement (useful for development, very noisy).
#   INFO  — Minimal SQL logging.
#   WARN  — Only warnings and errors.
# Hibernate SQL 日志级别。
LOG_HIBERNATE_LEVEL=DEBUG

# Application-specific log level for edu.asu.ser594.resumeassistant.
#   DEBUG — Prints request details, service calls, and exceptions.
#   INFO  — Normal operational messages.
#   WARN  — Only warnings and errors.
# 应用专属日志级别（edu.asu.ser594.resumeassistant）。
LOG_APP_LEVEL=DEBUG

# =============================================================================
# TIER 3: DATA LAYER (PostgreSQL + pgvector)
# =============================================================================
# PostgreSQL is the unified storage for relational business data and vector
# embeddings. The pgvector extension enables cosine-similarity search on
# high-dimensional vectors. This tier is completely isolated: only the
# backend can reach PostgreSQL via the dedicated db-network.
#
# Security:
#   - Port 5432 is NOT exposed to the host.
#   - Network isolation is Layer 1 of defense-in-depth.
#   - A strong password is Layer 2. Never use the default in production.
# =============================================================================

# Database name created on first container startup.
POSTGRES_DB=resume_assistant

# Database user. The backend connects with these credentials via JDBC.
POSTGRES_USER=resume_user

# Database password. Change this before any non-local deployment.
# The default `resume_pass` is safe for local development only.
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=resume_pass

# Docker DNS hostname of the PostgreSQL container. The backend JDBC URL
# uses this name, resolved on the isolated db-network.
POSTGRES_HOST=postgres

# PostgreSQL container port. NOT exposed to the host.
POSTGRES_PORT=5432
